==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: lateral pass
<hw>lat"er*al pass`</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Football)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A short pass to a
receiver who is upfield from the passer, i.e. is behind the passer
relative to the direction of the passer's goal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A part or extension of something that points
sideways, as a drift in a mine that goes to the side from the main
one.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lateral</ent>⟦br⟧
